<subSubSection id="C35C6510FFF6ED3D5231D45AA32954A1" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9369BFFF6ED3D5231D45AA32954A1" blockId="44.[264,1321,284,430]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFF6ED3D5231D45AA695543A" box="[312,414,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks</emphasis>
: Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFF6ED3D52E6D45AA55A543A" box="[495,593,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varna">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFF6ED3D52E6D45AA55A543A" box="[495,593,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">S. varna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFF6ED3D5185D45AA42F543A" box="[652,804,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolorata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFF6ED3D5185D45AA42F543A" box="[652,804,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">S. bicolorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20157F2FFF6ED3D5025D45AA48C5439" box="[812,903,284,310]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble each other externally and have very distinctive coloration. They also share the compressed aedeagus and the slender elongate needlelike paraphyses. 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFF6ED3D5181D42AA5E0548A" box="[648,747,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varna">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFF6ED3D5181D42AA5E0548A" box="[648,747,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">S. varna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not bear any process on the aedeagal shaft whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFF6ED3D5266D4D2A6E254A2" box="[367,489,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolorata">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFF6ED3D5266D4D2A6E254A2" box="[367,489,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">bicolorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a pair of slender, elongate, apical processes.
</paragraph>
